itself, such as bleeding or coronary artery injury, are reportedly low,5 and ongoing development of staplers or other devices for this purpose6 may reduce these risks further, although at some expense. There is increasing interest in the surgical community in adding LAAC, especially for patients with preoperative AF or mitral valve disease. However, there have been no large randomized surgical trials on this topic published thus far. Currently available reports are based only on small randomized trials
