Short-Term Outcomes Figure 2, A, shows the OR of 30-day or in-hospital
mortality. Among 7 studies, 4 were excluded because we were not able to calculate individual log ORs because of zero mortality in 1 of each group. The point estimate of OR for mortality was lower than 1 (favors LAAC) in all

the 3 studies included, and the overall OR was signiﬁcant,
with no signiﬁcant heterogeneity across the studies (OR, 0.384, 95% CI, 0.233-0.631, I2 0.0%, P ¼ .646).
Figure 2, B, shows the OR of 30-day or in-hospital CVA,
showing less CVA rates in the LAAC group (OR, 0.622, 95% CI, 0.388-0.998, I2 0.0%, P ¼ .917).

